Jami'ar Amurka ta zargi kasar Sin da "ta'addanci" tare da "tallace-tallace"
Wata mako bayan wani jaridar hukuma na kasar Sin ya wallafa sanarwar shafukan hudu a cikin jaridar yau da kullum na Amurka don inganta fa'idodin ciniki tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka, Donald Trump, ya yi magana a ranar Laraba da ya gabata game da karin biyan kuɗi na China Daily a Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi dacewa daga jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin shiga zaben 6 ga Nuwamba ga majalisar, tuhumar da China ta ƙaryata.
Shari'ar Trump cewa Beijing tana kokarin shiga zaben Amurka ta nuna farkon abin da hukumomin Amurka suka sanya a matsayin sabon mataki a yakin da Washington ke karuwa don matsawa China.
Kodayake al'ada gwamnatocin kasashen waje suna wallafa talla don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna rufe yakin kasuwanci na yau da kullum wanda ya ga bangarori biyu suna amfani da kudade akan shigo da juna.
An tsara farashin ritaya na kasar Sin a lokacin farkon yakin kasuwanci don rinjayar masu tallafawa a jihohin da ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican na Trump, in ji kwararrun Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, babban masana'antu na aikin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikata, manoma, da kamfanoni na Amurka.
Kasar Sin, ta rubuta Branstad a cikin labarin ra'ayi a Des Moines Register na Lahadi, "Yanzu yana sa ƙafafunsa a cikin gaggawa ta wannan tsõro tare da buga talla a cikin 'yan jarida kyauta."
"Tare da yada wannan talla, gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da' yancin jarida ta hanyar wallafa tallace-tallace da aka biya a Des Moines Register," in ji Branstad.
"Maimakon haka, a kan kujeru a nan a Beijing, mun sami muryar da ba ta dace ba kuma ba za mu taɓa ganin ainihin ra'ayin ra'ayi ba wanda Sin zasu iya samun tafarkin tattalin arzikin kasarsu, saboda kafofin sadarwa suna ƙarƙashin iko mai ƙarfi na Jam'iyyar Kwaminisanci ta China," in ji shi.
Bugu da ƙari, ya kara da cewa "wani daga cikin manyan jaridu na kasar Sin ya ƙi sadaukarwa" labarinsa, ko da yake bai bayyana abin da.
Jam'iyyar Republicans suna barin mata masu jefa kuri'a kafin zaben tsaka-tsaki tare da bala'i na Kavanaugh, suna gargadi masu tattaunawa
A lokacin da yawancin Jamhuriyar Republican ke tallafawa da kuma karewa da aka nada a Kotun Koli Bret Kavanaugh game da zargin da yawa na cin zarafin jima'i, masana sun yi gargadin cewa wannan zai iya haifar da mummunan amsa, musamman ma mata, a lokacin zaɓen da za a yi nan da nan.
Matsalolin da ke kewaye da lamarin sun kasance masu karfi sosai kuma mafi yawan 'yan Republican sun bayyana a fili cewa yana son ci gaba da zabe.
Wadannan abubuwa ba su da baya," ya ba da The Hill Grant Reeher, farfesa na kimiyyar siyasa a Maxwell School na Jami'ar Syracuse, don wani labarin da aka buga a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana da shakku cewa matsa lamba na ƙarshe na Senator Jeff Flake (Republican of Arizona) don gudanar da bincike na FBI ya isa ya sa masu jefa kuri'a masu fushi.
" Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru ba - ba za su manta da gobe ko a watan Nuwamba ba," in ji ranar Juma'a Karine Jean-Pierre, mai ba da shawara mai girma kuma mai magana da yawun ƙungiyar MoveOn na kasa, a cewar jaridar Washington, DC.
A ranar Litinin da safe, Protestants suna raira waƙa "Novembre ne a ƙofar!" lokacin da suke bayyana a majalisar dattijai, tun da yake Jam'iyyar da ke kula da kwamitin shari'a sun zaɓi su ci gaba da nadin Kavanaugh duk da shaidar Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, ya ruwaito Mic.
